  "prompt": "Writing a business plan, how do I estimate the customer base of my competitors?",
  "response": "To estimate your competitors' customer base, you can use several methods:\n\n1. Market Research Techniques\n- Industry reports\n- Market research databases\n- Public financial statements\n- Annual reports\n- Company websites\n- Social media analytics\n\n2. Indirect Estimation Methods\n- Analyze market share percentages\n- Review published revenue figures\n- Estimate customer numbers from public data\n- Check online review platforms\n- Examine social media followers/engagement\n\n3. Online Tools\n- SEMrush\n- SimilarWeb\n- LinkedIn company insights\n- Google Trends\n- Industry-specific tracking platforms\n\n4. Data Collection Strategies\n- Customer surveys\n- Trade association reports\n- Interviews with industry experts\n- Local business registries\n- Chamber of commerce resources\n\n5. Calculation Approaches\n- Revenue per customer estimation\n- Average transaction value analysis\n- Comparative market penetration rates\n- Customer acquisition cost evaluation\n\n6. Additional Research\n- Check business registration records\n- Review press releases\n- Analyze marketing campaign reach\n- Examine customer testimonials/case studies\n\nPro Tips:\n- Use multiple sources for cross-verification\n- Be conservative in estimations\n- Update research regularly\n- Consider both quantitative and qualitative data",
